name: Exeggcute
flavor_text: Though it may look like it’s just a bunch of eggs, it’s a proper Pokémon. Exeggcute communicates with others of its kind via telepathy, apparently.

name: Alolan Exeggutor
attack_effect: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.
flavor_text: Blazing sunlight has brought out the true form and powers of this Pokémon.

name: Surskit
attack_effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.
flavor_text: They usually live on ponds, but after an evening shower, they may appear on puddles in towns.

name: Masquerain
flavor_text: It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in any direction—to and fro and sideways.

name: Maractus
flavor_text: With noises that could be mistaken for the rattles of maracas, it creates an upbeat rhythm, startling bird Pokémon and making them fly off in a hurry.

name: Karrablast
flavor_text: Its strange physiology reacts to electrical energy in interesting ways. The presence of a Shelmet will cause this Pokémon to evolve.

name: Phantump
flavor_text: After a lost child perished in the forest, their spirit possessed a tree stump, causing the spirit’s rebirth as this Pokémon.

name: Trevenant
flavor_text: People fear it due to a belief that it devours any who try to cut down trees in its forest, but to the Pokémon it shares its woods with, it’s kind.

name: Rowlet
flavor_text: It sends its feathers, which are as sharp as blades, flying in attack. Its legs are strong, so its kicks are also formidable.

name: Rowlet
attack_effect: This attack does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.
flavor_text: It sends its feathers, which are as sharp as blades, flying in attack. Its legs are strong, so its kicks are also formidable.

name: Dartrix
flavor_text: This narcissistic Pokémon is a clean freak. If you don’t groom it diligently, it may stop listening to you.

name: Decidueye ex
attack_effect: This attack does 100 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon that have damage on them.

name: Grubbin
flavor_text: Its natural enemies, like Rookidee, may flee rather than risk getting caught in its large mandibles that can snap thick tree branches.

name: Fomantis
flavor_text: Fomantis hates having its naps interrupted. It fires off beams using energy it gathers by bathing in the sun.

name: Lurantis
attack_effect: This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon.
flavor_text: By masquerading as a bug Pokémon, it lowers the guard of actual bug Pokémon lured in by a scent of sweet flowers. Its sickles bring them down.

name: Morelull
flavor_text: Pokémon living in the forest eat the delicious caps on Morelull’s head. The caps regrow overnight.

name: Shiinotic
attack_effect: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.
flavor_text: Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing, it drains their vitality with its fingertips.

name: Bounsweet
flavor_text: Its sweat is sweet, like syrup made from boiled-down fruit. Because of this, Bounsweet was highly valued in the past, when sweeteners were scarce.

name: Steenee
attack_effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.
flavor_text: Steenee spreads a sweet scent that makes others feel invigorated. This same scent is popular for antiperspirants.

name: Tsareena
attack_effect: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.
flavor_text: This Pokémon is proud and aggressive. However, it is said that a Tsareena will instantly become calm if someone touches the crown on its calyx.

name: Wimpod
ability_effect: During your first turn, this Pokémon has no Retreat Cost.
flavor_text: It’s nature’s cleaner—it eats anything and everything,  including garbage and rotten things. The ground near  its nest is always clean.

name: Golisopod
attack_effect: If this Pokémon moved from your Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does 60 more damage.
flavor_text: It will do anything to win, taking advantage of every opening and finishing opponents off with the small claws on its front legs.

name: Dhelmise ex
attack_effect: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

name: Tapu Bulu
attack_effect: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.
flavor_text: Although it’s called a guardian deity, it’s violent enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.

name: Growlithe
flavor_text: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

name: Arcanine
flavor_text: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were captivated by its movement as it ran through prairies.

name: Alolan Marowak
attack_effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 70 damage for each heads. If at least 1 of them is heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.
flavor_text: This Pokémon sets the bone it holds on fire and dances through the night as a way to mourn its fallen allies.

name: Fletchinder
flavor_text: Fletchinder scatters embers in tall grass where bug Pokémon might be hiding and then catches them as they come leaping out.

name: Talonflame
flavor_text: It has top-notch flying capabilities. It flies around easily, even while carrying prey that weighs more than 220 lbs.

name: Litten
attack_effect: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.
flavor_text: If you try too hard to get close to it, it won’t open up to you. Even if you do grow close, giving it too much affection is still a no-no.

name: Litten
flavor_text: If you try too hard to get close to it, it won’t open up to you. Even if you do grow close, giving it too much affection is still a no-no.

name: Torracat
attack_effect: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.
flavor_text: Torracat will let its Trainer coddle it once they’ve grown close, but it’s a powerful, sharp-clawed Pokémon, so its Trainer gets covered in scratches.

name: Incineroar ex
attack_effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Oricorio
attack_effect: Discard a random Energy from both Active Pokémon.
flavor_text: This form of Oricorio has sipped red nectar. It whips up blazing flames as it moves to the steps of its passionate dance.

name: Salandit
flavor_text: It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow, rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic gas to make them dizzy and take them down.

name: Salazzle
attack_effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned and Burned.
flavor_text: Salazzle makes its opponents light-headed with poisonous gas, then captivates them with alluring movements to turn them into loyal servants.

name: Turtonator
attack_effect: Discard a [R] Energy from this Pokémon.
flavor_text: Explosive substances coat the shell on its back. Enemies that dare attack it will be blown away by an immense detonation.

name: Alolan Sandshrew
flavor_text: Life on mountains covered with deep snow has granted this Pokémon a body of ice that’s as hard as steel.

name: Alolan Sandslash
attack_effect: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack, do 40 damage to the Attacking Pokémon.
flavor_text: It uses large, hooked claws to cut a path through deep snow as it runs. On snowy mountains, this Sandslash is faster than any other Pokémon.

name: Alolan Vulpix
attack_effect: Take a [W] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.
flavor_text: After long years in the ever-snowcapped mountains of Alola, this Vulpix has gained power over ice.

name: Alolan Ninetales
attack_effect: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.
flavor_text: A deity resides in the snowy mountains where this Pokémon lives. In ancient times, it was worshiped as that deity’s incarnation.

name: Shellder
flavor_text: It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond. Inside, however, it is surprisingly tender.

name: Cloyster
attack_effect: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes −20 damage from attacks.
flavor_text: Cloyster that live in seas with harsh tidal currents grow large, sharp spikes on their shells.

name: Lapras
flavor_text: A smart and kindhearted Pokémon, it glides across the surface of the sea while its beautiful song echoes around it.

name: Popplio
attack_effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.
flavor_text: The balloons it inflates with its nose grow larger and larger as it practices day by day.

name: Popplio
flavor_text: The balloons it inflates with its nose grow larger and larger as it practices day by day.

name: Brionne
flavor_text: It gets excited when it sees a dance it doesn’t know. This hard worker practices diligently until it can learn that dance.

name: Primarina
ability_effect: Once during your turn, you may heal 30 damage from each of your [W] Pokémon.
flavor_text: To Primarina, every battle is a stage. It takes down its prey with beautiful singing and dancing.

name: Crabominable ex
attack_effect: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Insatiable Striking attack does +40 damage.

name: Wishiwashi
attack_effect: Put 1 random Wishiwashi or Wishiwashi ex from your deck onto your Bench.
flavor_text: Individually, they’re incredibly weak. It’s by gathering up into schools that they’re able to confront opponents.

name: Wishiwashi ex
attack_effect: This attack does 40 more damage for each of your Benched Wishiwashi or Wishiwashi ex.

name: Dewpider
flavor_text: It forms a water bubble at the rear of its body and then covers its head with it. Meeting another Dewpider means comparing water-bubble sizes.

name: Araquanid
attack_effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Basic Pokemon, this attack does 60 more damage.
flavor_text: It launches water bubbles with its legs, drowning prey within the bubbles. This Pokémon can then take its time to savor its meal.

name: Pyukumuku
ability_effect: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, do 50 damage to the Attacking Pokémon.
flavor_text: It lives in warm, shallow waters. If it encounters a foe, it will spit out its internal organs as a means to punch them.

name: Bruxish
flavor_text: It grinds its teeth with great force to stimulate its brain. It fires the psychic energy created by this process from the protuberance on its head.

name: Tapu Fini
attack_effect: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.
flavor_text: This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog, it came to be both feared and revered.

name: Pikachu
flavor_text: When it is angered, it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

name: Alolan Raichu ex
attack_effect: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Alolan Geodude
flavor_text: If you mistake it for a rock and step on it, it will headbutt you in anger. In addition to the pain, it will also zap you with a shock.

name: Alolan Graveler
flavor_text: When two Graveler fight each other, it fills the surroundings with flashes of light and sound. People call it the “fireworks of the earth.”

name: Alolan Golem
attack_effect: Discard 2 [L] Energy from this Pokémon.
flavor_text: It’s grumpy and stubborn. If you upset it, it discharges electricity from the surface of its body and growls with a voice like thunder.

name: Helioptile
flavor_text: When spread, the frills on its head act like solar panels, generating the power behind this Pokémon’s electric moves.

name: Heliolisk
flavor_text: One Heliolisk basking in the sun with its frill outspread is all it would take to produce enough electricity to power a city.

name: Charjabug
flavor_text: While its durable shell protects it from attacks, Charjabug strikes at enemies with jolts of electricity discharged from the tips of its jaws.

name: Vikavolt
attack_effect: During your opponent's next turn, they can't play any Item cards from their hand.
flavor_text: It builds up electricity in its abdomen, focuses it through its jaws, and then fires the electricity off in concentrated beams.

name: Oricorio
ability_effect: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon ex.
flavor_text: This form of Oricorio has sipped yellow nectar. It uses nimble steps to approach opponents, then knocks them out with electric punches.

name: Togedemaru
attack_effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.
flavor_text: With the long hairs on its back, this Pokémon takes in electricity from other electric Pokémon. It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

name: Tapu Koko
attack_effect: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched [L] Pokémon.
flavor_text: Although it’s called a guardian deity, if a person or Pokémon puts it in a bad mood, it will become a malevolent deity and attack.

name: Mr. Mime
attack_effect: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from—and effects of—attacks done to this Pokémon.
flavor_text: The broadness of its hands may be no coincidence—many scientists believe its palms became enlarged specifically for pantomiming.

name: Sableye
attack_effect: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.
flavor_text: It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.

name: Spoink
attack_effect: Take a [P] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.
flavor_text: Spoink will die if it stops bouncing. The pearl on its head amplifies its psychic powers.

name: Grumpig
flavor_text: It can perform odd dance steps to influence foes. Its style of dancing became hugely popular overseas.

name: Lunatone
flavor_text: The phase of the moon apparently has some effect on its power. It’s active on the night of a full moon.

name: Shuppet
flavor_text: It loves to feed on feelings like envy and malice. Its upright horn catches the emotions of people.

name: Banette
attack_effect: During your opponent's next turn, they can't take any Energy from their Energy Zone to attach to their Active Pokémon.
flavor_text: This Pokémon developed from an abandoned doll that amassed a grudge. It is seen in dark alleys.

name: Oricorio
attack_effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.
flavor_text: This form of Oricorio has sipped pink nectar. It elevates its mind with the gentle steps of its dance, then unleashes its psychic energy.

name: Oricorio
attack_effect: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 60 more damage.
flavor_text: This form of Oricorio has sipped purple nectar. It uses ethereal dance steps to call forth the spirits of the dead.

name: Cutiefly
flavor_text: Nectar and pollen are its favorite fare. In fields of flowers, it gets into skirmishes with Butterfree over food.

name: Ribombee
flavor_text: It makes pollen puffs from pollen and nectar. The puffs’ effects depend on the type of ingredients and how much of each one is used.

name: Comfey
ability_effect: Each of your Pokémon that has any [P] Energy attached recovers from all Special Conditions and can't be affected by any Special Conditions.
flavor_text: Comfey picks flowers with its vine and decorates itself with them. For some reason, flowers won’t wither once they’re attached to a Comfey.

name: Sandygast
flavor_text: If it loses its shovel, it will stick something else—like a branch—in its head to make do until it finds another shovel.

name: Palossand
flavor_text: The terrifying Palossand drags smaller Pokémon into its sandy body. Once its victims are trapped, it drains them of their vitality whenever it pleases.

name: Mimikyu
attack_effect: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your Pokémon.
flavor_text: There was a scientist who peeked under Mimikyu’s old rag in the name of research. The scientist died of a mysterious disease.

name: Tapu Lele
attack_effect: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon for each Energy attached to that Pokémon.
flavor_text: It heals the wounds of people and Pokémon by sprinkling them with its sparkling scales. This guardian deity is worshiped on Akala.

name: Cosmog
attack_effect: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
flavor_text: Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown away by the slightest breeze, it doesn’t seem to care.

name: Cosmoem
attack_effect: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes −50 damage from attacks.
flavor_text: The king who ruled Alola in times of antiquity called it the “cocoon of the stars” and built an altar to worship it.

name: Lunala ex
ability_effect: Once during your turn, you may move all [P] Energy from 1 of your Benched [P] Pokémon to your Active Pokémon.

name: Necrozma
attack_effect: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.
flavor_text: It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light, which serves as its energy. It’s apparently from another world.

name: Cubone
flavor_text: When the memory of its departed mother brings it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the skull it wears on its head.

name: Makuhita
flavor_text: It grows stronger by enduring harsh training. It is a gutsy Pokémon that can withstand any attack.

name: Hariyama
attack_effect: Switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)
flavor_text: It loves challenging others to tests of strength. It has the power to stop a train with a slap.

name: Solrock
flavor_text: When it rotates itself, it gives off light similar to the sun, thus blinding its foes.

name: Drilbur
flavor_text: It brings its claws together and whirls around at high speed before rushing toward its prey.

name: Timburr
flavor_text: It loves helping out with construction projects. It loves it so much that if rain causes work to halt, it swings its log around and throws a tantrum.

name: Gurdurr
flavor_text: It shows off its muscles to Machoke and other Gurdurr. If it fails to measure up to the other Pokémon, it lies low for a little while.

name: Conkeldurr
ability_effect: If this Pokémon would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, flip a coin. If heads, this Pokémon is not Knocked Out, and its remaining HP becomes 10.
flavor_text: Concrete mixed by Conkeldurr is much more durable than normal concrete, even when the compositions of the two materials are the same.

name: Crabrawler
flavor_text: This Pokémon punches trees and eats the berries that drop down, training itself and getting food at the same time.

name: Rockruff
attack_effect: Put a random card that evolves from Rockruff from your deck into your hand.
flavor_text: This Pokémon is very friendly when it’s young. Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures, but it never forgets the kindness of its master.

name: Rockruff
flavor_text: This Pokémon is very friendly when it’s young. Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures, but it never forgets the kindness of its master.

name: Lycanroc
attack_effect: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a random Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.
flavor_text: Lycanroc attacks its prey with its sharp claws and fangs. It loyally obeys the instructions of a Trainer it trusts.

name: Lycanroc
attack_effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has more remaining HP than this Pokémon, this attack does 50 more damage.
flavor_text: This Pokémon uses its rocky mane to slash any who approach. It will even disobey its Trainer if it dislikes the orders it was given.

name: Mudbray
flavor_text: This Pokémon covers itself in mud that it has regurgitated. The mud won’t dry out even if it’s exposed to the sun for a long time.

name: Mudsdale
attack_effect: This Pokémon also does 40 damage to itself.
flavor_text: This Pokémon has been treasured not just for its physical labor but also because it produces high-quality mud used for making pottery.

name: Passimian ex
ability_effect: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, move all [F] Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Minior
attack_effect: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.
flavor_text: Places where Minior fall from the night sky are few and far between, with Alola being one of the precious few.

name: Alolan Rattata
flavor_text: It shows no interest in anything that isn’t fresh. If you take it shopping with you, it will help you pick out ingredients.

name: Alolan Raticate
attack_effect: Discard a random Item card from your opponent's hand.
flavor_text: It has an incredibly greedy personality. Its nest is filled with so much food gathered by Rattata at its direction, it can’t possibly eat it all.

name: Alolan Meowth
flavor_text: It’s accustomed to luxury because it used to live with Alolan royalty. As a result, it’s very picky about food.

name: Alolan Persian
ability_effect: This Pokémon takes −20 damage from attacks.
flavor_text: The round face of Alolan Persian is considered to be a symbol of prosperity in the Alola region, so these Pokémon are very well cared for.

name: Alolan Grimer
flavor_text: There are a hundred or so of them living in Alola’s waste-disposal site. They’re all hard workers who eat a lot of trash.

name: Alolan Muk ex
attack_effect: 1 Special Condition from among Asleep, Burned, Confused, Paralyzed, and Poisoned is chosen at random, and your opponent's Active Pokémon is now affected by that Special Condition. Any Special Conditions already affecting that Pokémon will not be chosen.

name: Absol
attack_effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 60 more damage.
flavor_text: Swift as the wind, Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved, bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.

name: Trubbish
flavor_text: Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around, you could even find one of these Pokémon living in your room.

name: Garbodor
attack_effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.
flavor_text: This Pokémon eats trash, which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.

name: Mareanie
flavor_text: This Pokémon wanders the seaside looking for food. It often gets electric shocks from broken Pincurchin spines that it tries to eat.

name: Toxapex
attack_effect: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.
flavor_text: This Pokémon lives within a dome made by its own legs. Toxapex monitors its surroundings by sensing the flow of the tide through its spikes.

name: Alolan Diglett
flavor_text: The metal-rich geology of this Pokémon’s habitat caused it to develop steel whiskers on its head.

name: Alolan Dugtrio
attack_effect: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 70 damage for each heads.
flavor_text: Their beautiful, metallic whiskers create a sort of protective helmet on their heads, and they also function as highly precise sensors.

name: Excadrill
flavor_text: It’s not uncommon for tunnels that appear to have formed naturally to actually be a result of Excadrill’s rampant digging.

name: Escavalier
attack_effect: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.
flavor_text: Wearing the shell covering they stole from Shelmet, they defend themselves and attack with two lances.

name: Klefki
attack_effect: Draw a card.
flavor_text: Once it absorbs a key’s metal ions, it discards the key without a second thought. However, it will hang on to keys it favors for decades.

name: Solgaleo ex
attack_effect: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.
ability_effect: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may switch it with your Active Pokémon.

name: Magearna
attack_effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has an Ability, this attack does 40 more damage.
flavor_text: It synchronizes its consciousness with others to understand their feelings. This faculty makes it useful for taking care of people.

name: Drampa
attack_effect: If any of your Benched Pokémon have damage on them, this attack does 50 more damage.
flavor_text: The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.

name: Jangmo-o
flavor_text: They learn to fight by smashing their head scales together. The dueling strengthens both their skills and their spirits.

name: Hakamo-o
flavor_text: The scaleless, scarred parts of its body are signs of its strength. It shows them off to defeated opponents.

name: Kommo-o
attack_effect: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes +30 damage from attacks.
flavor_text: It clatters its tail scales to unnerve opponents. This Pokémon will battle only those who stand steadfast in the face of this display.

name: Tauros
attack_effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage.
flavor_text: When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails, it’s a warning that the Pokémon is about to charge with astounding speed.

name: Skitty
flavor_text: It can’t stop itself from chasing moving things, and it runs in a circle, chasing its own tail.

name: Delcatty
attack_effect: Take a [C] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
flavor_text: It dislikes dirty places. It often searches for a comfortable place in which to groom itself.

name: Fletchling
flavor_text: This Pokémon is normally calm, but once it enters battle, its hormonal balance changes and it becomes aggressive.

name: Hawlucha
attack_effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a [D] Pokémon, this attack does 30 more damage.
flavor_text: Its elegant finishing moves—performed by nimbly leaping around using its wings—are polished in the forest where it was born and raised.

name: Pikipek
flavor_text: It pecks at trees with its hard beak. You can get some idea of its mood or condition from the rhythm of its pecking.

name: Trumbeak
flavor_text: It can bend the tip of its beak to produce over a hundred different cries at will.

name: Toucannon
flavor_text: They smack beaks with others of their kind to communicate. The strength and number of hits tell each other how they feel.

name: Yungoos
flavor_text: Its stomach fills most of its torso. It wanders the same path every day, searching for fresh food.

name: Gumshoos
flavor_text: Once it finds signs of prey, it will patiently stake out the location, waiting until the sun goes down.

name: Stufful
flavor_text: Its fluffy fur is a delight to pet, but carelessly reaching out to touch this Pokémon could result in painful retaliation.

name: Bewear
attack_effect: This Pokémon is now Confused.
flavor_text: Once it accepts you as a friend, it tries to show its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is dangerous—it could easily shatter your bones.

name: Oranguru
attack_effect: During your opponent's next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokémon cost 1 [C] more, and its Retreat Cost is 1 [C] more.
flavor_text: People used to mistake Oranguru for a human when they saw it issue command after command to the other Pokémon of the forest.

name: Komala
ability_effect: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, whenever you attach an Energy from your Energy Zone to it, it is now Asleep.
flavor_text: Komala spends its entire life sleeping. It feeds on leaves that contain a potent poison only Komala can break down.

name: Regirock
ability_effect: This Pokémon takes −20 damage from attacks.
flavor_text: Every bit of Regirock’s body is made of stone. As parts of its body erode, this Pokémon sticks rocks to itself to repair what’s been lost.

name: Cranidos
flavor_text: A primeval Pokémon, it possesses a hard and sturdy skull, lacking any intelligence within.

name: Rampardos
attack_effect: If your opponent's Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from this attack, this Pokémon also does 50 damage to itself.
flavor_text: In ancient times, people would dig up fossils of this Pokémon and use its skull, which is harder than steel, to make helmets.

name: Wormadam
flavor_text: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.

name: Riolu
flavor_text: They communicate with one another using their auras. They are able to run all through the night.

name: Lucario
ability_effect: Attacks used by your [F] Pokémon do +20 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.
flavor_text: It’s said that no foe can remain invisible to Lucario, since it can detect auras—even those of foes it could not otherwise see.

name: Hippopotas
flavor_text: It shuts its nostrils tight, then travels through sand as if walking. They form colonies of around 10.

name: Hippowdon
flavor_text: It is surprisingly quick to anger. It holds its mouth agape as a display of its strength.

name: Gallade ex
attack_effect: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Murkrow
flavor_text: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

name: Honchkrow
attack_effect: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.
flavor_text: It is merciless by nature. It is said that it never forgives the mistakes of its Murkrow followers.

name: Sneasel
attack_effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.
flavor_text: This cunning Pokémon hides under the cover of darkness, waiting to attack its prey.

name: Weavile ex
attack_effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has damage on it, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Poochyena
flavor_text: A Pokémon with a persistent nature, it chases its chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.

name: Mightyena
flavor_text: It will always obey the commands of a skilled Trainer. Its behavior arises from its living in packs in ancient times.

name: Stunky
flavor_text: It sprays a foul fluid from its rear. Its stench spreads over a mile radius, driving Pokémon away.

name: Skuntank
attack_effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.
flavor_text: It attacks by spraying a horribly smelly fluid from the tip of its tail. Attacks from above confound it.

name: Spiritomb
attack_effect: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon.
flavor_text: Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.

name: Skorupi
flavor_text: After burrowing into the sand, it waits patiently for prey to come near. This Pokémon and Sizzlipede share common descent.

name: Drapion
attack_effect: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads. If at least 2 of them are heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.
flavor_text: Its poison is potent, but it rarely sees use. This Pokémon prefers to use physical force instead, going on rampages with its car-crushing strength.

name: Croagunk
attack_effect: Flip a coin for each Pokémon you have in play. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.
flavor_text: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.

name: Toxicroak
attack_effect: Flip a coin for each Pokémon you have in play. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.
flavor_text: Swaying and dodging the attacks of its foes, it weaves its flexible body in close, then lunges out with its poisonous claws.

name: Darkrai
attack_effect: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.
flavor_text: It chases people and Pokémon from its territory by causing them to experience deep, nightmarish slumbers.

name: Darkrai ex
ability_effect: Whenever you attach a [D] Energy from your Energy Zone to this Pokémon, do 20 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Skarmory
attack_effect: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 30 more damage.
flavor_text: People fashion swords from Skarmory’s shed feathers, so this Pokémon is a popular element in heraldic designs.

name: Registeel
flavor_text: Registeel’s body is made of a strange material that is flexible enough to stretch and shrink but also more durable than any metal.

name: Shieldon
flavor_text: A mild-mannered, herbivorous Pokémon, it used its face to dig up tree roots to eat. The skin on its face was plenty tough.

name: Bastiodon
ability_effect: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks, flip a coin. If heads, this Pokémon takes −100 damage from that attack.
flavor_text: The bones of its face are huge and hard, so they were mistaken for its spine until after this Pokémon was successfully restored.

name: Wormadam
attack_effect: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.
flavor_text: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.

name: Bronzor
flavor_text: Ancient people believed that the pattern on Bronzor’s back contained a mysterious power.

name: Bronzong
attack_effect: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes −20 damage from attacks.
flavor_text: In ages past, this Pokémon was revered as a bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.

name: Probopass
attack_effect: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 50 more damage for each heads.
flavor_text: Although it can control its units known as Mini-Noses, they sometimes get lost and don’t come back.

name: Dialga ex
attack_effect: Take 2 [M] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Heatran
attack_effect: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.
flavor_text: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

name: Gible
flavor_text: It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.

name: Gabite
flavor_text: In rare cases, it molts and sheds its scales. Medicine containing its scales as an ingredient will make a weary body feel invigorated.

name: Garchomp
ability_effect: You must discard a card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw a card.
flavor_text: It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.

name: Lickitung
flavor_text: If this Pokémon’s sticky saliva gets on you and you don’t clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won’t go away, either.

name: Lickilicky ex
attack_effect: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 40 more damage for each heads.

name: Eevee
attack_effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.
flavor_text: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Porygon
flavor_text: State-of-the-art technology was used to create Porygon. It was the first artificial Pokémon to be created via computer programming.

name: Porygon2
flavor_text: This is a Porygon that was updated with special data. Porygon2 develops itself by learning about many different subjects all on its own.

name: Porygon-Z
attack_effect: Change the type of the next Energy that will be generated for your opponent to 1 of the following at random: [G],[R],[W],[L],[P],[F],[D], or [M].
flavor_text: Porygon-Z had a program installed to allow it to move between dimensions, but the program also caused instability in Porygon-Z’s behavior.

name: Aipom
flavor_text: As it did more and more with its tail, its hands became clumsy. It makes its nest high in the treetops.

name: Ambipom
attack_effect: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.
flavor_text: It uses its tails for everything. If it wraps both of its tails around you and gives you a squeeze, that’s proof it really likes you.

name: Starly
attack_effect: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokémon.
flavor_text: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.

name: Staravia
flavor_text: Recognizing their own weakness, they always live in a group. When alone, a Staravia cries noisily.

name: Staraptor
attack_effect: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.
flavor_text: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

name: Bidoof
attack_effect: Halve your opponent's Active Pokémon's remaining HP, rounded down.
flavor_text: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.

name: Bibarel
flavor_text: It busily makes its nest with stacks of branches and roots it has cut up with its sharp incisors.

name: Buneary
flavor_text: If both of Buneary’s ears are rolled up, something is wrong with its body or mind. It’s a sure sign the Pokémon is in need of care.

name: Lopunny
attack_effect: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.
flavor_text: Lopunny is constantly monitoring its surroundings. If danger approaches, this Pokémon responds with superdestructive kicks.

name: Glameow
attack_effect: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.
flavor_text: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.

name: Purugly
attack_effect: Your opponent reveals their hand. Choose a card you find there and shuffle it into your opponent's deck.
flavor_text: It would claim another Pokémon’s nest as its own if it finds a nest sufficiently comfortable.

name: Chatot
attack_effect: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.
flavor_text: It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to trick them into thinking it’s one of them. This way they won’t attack it.

name: Fan Rotom
attack_effect: Flip a coin. If heads, put your opponent's Active Pokémon into their hand.
flavor_text: This Rotom has entered an electric fan. It smirks with satisfaction over a prank well pulled after it blows away everything around it.

name: Regigigas
attack_effect: This attack does more damage equal to the damage this Pokémon has on it.
flavor_text: It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.

name: Tangrowth
attack_effect: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.
flavor_text: Tangrowth has two arms that it can extend as it pleases. Recent research has shown that these arms are, in fact, bundles of vines.

name: Combee
attack_effect: Put 1 random Basic Pokémon from your deck onto your Bench.
flavor_text: At night, Combee sleep in a group of about a hundred, packed closely together in a lump.

name: Carnivine
attack_effect: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 more damage.
flavor_text: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

name: Shaymin
ability_effect: Once during your turn, you may heal 10 damage from each of your Pokémon.
flavor_text: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

name: Mamoswine
ability_effect: This Pokémon takes −30 damage from attacks from [R] or [W] Pokémon.
flavor_text: This Pokémon can be spotted in wall paintings from as far back as 10,000 years ago. For a while, it was thought to have gone extinct.

name: Gastrodon
attack_effect: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.
flavor_text: They normally inhabit rocky seashores, but in times of continuous rain, they can sometimes be found in the mountains, far from the sea.

name: Manaphy
attack_effect: Choose 2 of your Benched Pokémon. For each of those Pokémon, take a [W] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to that Pokémon.
flavor_text: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.

name: Shinx
attack_effect: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from—and effects of—attacks done to this Pokémon.
flavor_text: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.

name: Rotom
attack_effect: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 30 more damage.
flavor_text: Its electricity-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.

name: Drifloon
attack_effect: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes −20 damage from attacks.
flavor_text: It is whispered that any child who mistakes Drifloon for a balloon and holds on to it could wind up missing.

name: Mesprit
attack_effect: You can use this attack only if you have Uxie and Azelf on your Bench. Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.
flavor_text: Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

name: Giratina
ability_effect: If this Pokémon has any Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.
flavor_text: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.

name: Cresselia
attack_effect: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.
flavor_text: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

attack_effect: Discard the top 3 cards of your deck.

attack_effect: Take a [G] Energy from your Energy Zone and attach it to this Pokémon.

attack_effect: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.
flavor_text: Each of Exeggutor’s three heads is thinking different thoughts. The three don’t seem to be very interested in one another.
